Manages a dedicated mode domain resource within HuaweiCloud.

> **NOTE:** All WAF resources depend on WAF instances, and the WAF instances need to be purchased before they can be
used. The dedicated mode domain name resource can be used in Dedicated Mode and ELB Mode.

        final var dedicatedEngineId = config.get("dedicatedEngineId");

<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#type_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>Server network type, IPv4 or IPv6. Valid values are: <code>ipv4</code> and <code>ipv6</code>. Changing
this creates a new service.</p>
</dd><dt class="property-required property-replacement"
            title="Required">
        <span id="vpcid_yaml">
<a data-swiftype-name="resource-property" data-swiftype-type="text" href="#vpcid_yaml" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">vpc<wbr>Id</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">String</span>
    </dt>
    <dd><p>The id of the vpc used by the server. Changing this creates a service.</p>
</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

## Import



Dedicated mode domain can be imported using the `id`, e.g.

```sh
 $ pulumi import huaweicloud:Waf/dedicatedDomain:DedicatedDomain domain_1 69e9a86becb4424298cc6bdeacbf69d5
```
